results.extract: List of public drinking fountain taps in Brisbane.

resources.description:
This dataset represents all publicly available taps in Brisbane City Council Parks. This dataset does not include water fountains available at Council Community Halls, Pools, or Libraries. We have included “Combination Taps” in this dataset. These are taps that are water bubblers, as well as publicly accessible water taps. We have not included a list of Brisbane City Council maintenance taps, which require a staff key to operate.

The following columns are included:

- Ward: Which Ward in Brisbane the tap/bubbler is located in
- Suburb: Which suburb in Brisbane the tap/bubbler is located in
- Property Code: We have included the property code so that in the future, when we add additional parks datasets a correlation can be made. We hope to post a table of Property Code look up shortly
- Park Name: The name of the Brisbane Park where the tap/bubbler is located.
- Node ID: We have included the Node ID so that in the future, when we add additional parks datasets a correlation can be made
- Node Name: This narrows down to specific locations within parks and can be useful when looking at our larger parks
- Item ID: This could be useful in future solutions that feed back to Council systems. It is a unique identifying in our Council database for that park asset
- Item Name: The name of the item, which in this case is “Bubbler/Fountain” (a water fountain) or “Tap Combination”(a water fountain and publicly accessible water tap combination)
- Item Description: This includes any information that may have been collected by field services about this park asset and is a free form field
- Easting/Northing: This is the geo-location information
- Lat/Long: Latitude and Longitude coordinates.
resources.name: Drinking fountain taps
